00:30:58,067 --> 00:30:59,710
And they were surprised to find that

250
00:31:00,230 --> 00:31:21,646
they'd overcome their trauma it wasn't for them for people of eastern mentality you know like it wasn't such a huge trauma that it would be say to a westerner because they accept they have the attitude of karma they have the attitude of impermanence everything's impermanent what's the problem see

251
00:31:22,133 --> 00:31:29,738
It doesn't mean to say they don't suffer the loss of loved ones and all that, but there isn't this ongoing post-traumatic stress.

252
00:31:30,278 --> 00:31:34,152
See, all that's gone because of that easy acceptance of the way things are.

253
00:31:36,763 --> 00:31:42,479
So now we, you see, constantly reminding ourselves that there is impermanence.

254
00:31:42,779 --> 00:31:43,643
Everything is impermanent.

255
00:31:43,663 --> 00:31:47,432
You simply do not know what's going to happen in the next moment.

256
00:31:47,553 --> 00:31:48,315
You just don't know.

