00:32:35,208 --> 00:32:38,373
See?

268
00:32:38,393 --> 00:32:40,135
I had a case of...

269
00:32:40,395 --> 00:32:43,740
I have a very strange sense of humour, but...

270
00:32:44,842 --> 00:32:45,903
There was a...

271
00:32:46,660 --> 00:32:50,548
Somebody I know is very, she was about 70-odd.

272
00:32:50,568 --> 00:32:56,262
And she met an old-time sweetheart, going way back to her early days.

273
00:32:57,085 --> 00:33:01,736
And, I mean, I got this story, you know, secondhand.

274
00:33:01,756 --> 00:33:03,740
And, well, they fell in love, you know.

275
00:33:04,430 --> 00:33:33,339
and they got married and she brought all her stuff over from America a couple of thousand pounds they set up in this beautiful I went to visit them actually they set up in this lovely little cottage in a nice little tweed country village you know English country village and not so long married I mean you know come of a certain age one has to accept things it seems as though he was just going for the toast out of the toaster when he collapsed

276
00:33:33,843 --> 00:33:42,673
And I've always thought of the horror of dying as you're grabbing hold of a piece of toast.

277
00:33:45,336 --> 00:33:59,692
As you're lifting the piece of toast with marmalade to your mouth, unable to clamp your jaw over it.

278
